# HSC Grammar Rules

Upload your HSC grammar rules here following this structure:

```
/content/rules/hsc/
├── tense/
│   └── rules.json
├── voice/
│   └── rules.json
├── narration/
│   └── rules.json
├── modifiers/
│   └── rules.json
└── ...
```

## JSON File Format

Each rules.json file should contain:

```json
{
  "topic": "Tense",
  "rules": [
    {
      "title": "Present Simple Tense",
      "content": "The present simple tense is used for habitual actions, general truths, and permanent situations...",
      "examples": [
        "I go to school every day.",
        "The sun rises in the east.",
        "Water boils at 100°C."
      ],
      "tips": [
        "Use base form of verb for I, you, we, they",
        "Add -s/-es for he, she, it",
        "Use 'do/does' for questions and negatives"
      ]
    }
  ]
}
```